pr_body:
- [x]  The non-default options should be visually marked, e.g., by bolding the value. 
- [x] After removing my json config file, I got an error on opening the editor:
```
  File "mslib/msui/mss_pyui.py", line 743, in open_config_editor
    self.config_editor = editor.ConfigurationEditorWindow(parent=self)
  File "/home/icg173/src/mss/mslib/msui/editor.py", line 152, in __init__
    if json_file_data:
UnboundLocalError: local variable 'json_file_data' referenced before assignment
```
- [x] For the "grouping" of configuration options, we need to come up with "categories" for the drop-down box. Not necessarily your task, though.
- [x] Because changing the configuration requires a restart I would suggest to make the Editor a blocking dialogue.
- [x] Pushing the "+ Add" "Restore Defaults" and "Import" buttons does not seem to do anything???
- [x] Add more logging.debug messages to roughly allow tracing the code execution from the log on the terminal (after calling with --debug)
- [x] The whole "buttonbox" does not seem to be working? Where is the code handling the buttons? I would suggest implementing the buttons "manually" With QPushButtons. (edited) 
- [x] It would be nice, not essentiaol  if you would follow the naming style of the old UI. See e.g.  mslib/msui/ui/ui_topview_window.ui I.e. ComboBoxes are named "cb"Whatever and pushbuttons "pb"SomethinElse.
- [x] The documentaion should be displayed with some stand-in text (like document me)
- [x] I propose to decouple the Adding of Options from the Filter. If one has selected a list-like option (i.e. it is highlighted with a bar), the add option should become clickable. I.e. Add/Remove should be enabled/disabled depending on if they can actually act. Rename the filter to be obviously "only" a filter.
- [x] "Project->Project Properties->Edit Project" does not seem to do anything.

pr_title: GSoC config editor update 3 - refactor of config_loader
pr_body: I have attempted to refactor the order in which configuration is loaded. With the changes I've made, the settings is now read only once while starting the app, and is updated whenever restarted.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 692226382, 'comment_body': 'removed lines intended?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 19, 15, 26, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ReimarBauer', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 692231074, 'comment_body': 'tests needs also be splitted in multiple modules
preferable we should have "module"  and "test_module"
the current tests.py is a placeholder from the long file.

', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 19, 15, 29, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ReimarBauer', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 692252700, 'comment_body': "with global I'm very carefully and I had already a lot of the problems here

", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 19, 15, 45, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ReimarBauer', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 692290683, 'comment_body': 'I removed this because this shortcut applies only for mac. I think the use is justified here. Please not that you do not need it here, actually, as user_options is a dictionary, which you might modify in-place. 
E.g.
`
copied_config = copy.deepcopy(user_options)
user_options.clear()
user_config.update(copied_config)
`
or similar.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 20, 8, 51, 43, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'joernu76', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 692782864, 'comment_body': 'global not needed here, I think.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 20, 8, 52, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'joernu76', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 692783828, 'comment_body': "wouldn't it make sense to move the config class here? "State" in any form is "evil", IMHO, but functional programming languages (e.g. Haskell) lacking state have somehow problems of not being adopted due to being very difficult to work with.
